    "recap_headline": "University of Richmond Athletics",
    "recap_text": "BRONX, NY \u2013\nRichmond baseball had two two-run home runs on the day, but it wasn't enough Friday afternoon as the Spiders fell 8-4 to the Fordham Rams at Houlihan Park.\nRichmond, now 11-11 on the year and 0-4 in league play, and Fordham, 10-10 and 3-1, will match-up again Saturday for a 1 p.m. contest at Houlihan Park. The game will be streamed on ESPN+.\nUR starter\nChase Topolski\nkept the Rams off the board for eight outs, but the Rams tagged him for two runs in the third to take the lead. Fordham added two more runs off him in with two outs in the fourth. Topolski allowed four runs on four hits, three walks and collected four strikeouts over four innings of work.\nDylan Winebrenner\nlaunched his seventh home run with two outs in the top of the fifth, pushing in\nEvan Wilson\nwho reached on a fielder's choice to collect RBI 16 and 17 on the season.\nThe Rams picked up runs off Spider relievers\nAngel Santiago-Cruz\nin the fifth and\nGlenn Smith\nin the sixth and seventh innings. Santiago-Cruz allowed one run on one hit, a walk and a strikeout in an inning of work. Smith got tagged three runs on five hits and two walks in two innings of work.\nPaul Witkop\ntossed a scoreless eighth with a walk.\nIn the top of the ninth, Wilson collected his third hit of the day with a two-run home run, his second of the year, to right center to make it 8-4.\nReid Downs\n, who drew a walk to lead off the inning, scored on the home run.",
